title: For Sale:  Bersa BP9CC as new in box compact carry 9mm
postcontent:
Overall dimensions for the BP9CC are 6.35-inches long, 4.8-inches tall and 0.94-inches wide. It weighs 21.1 ounces, unloaded, and has a 3.3-inch barrel. External controls include an ambidextrous magazine release button—in its usual position just behind the trigger guard—a disassembly pin and a key-operated locking safety. Other safety features are the loaded-chamber indicator—a metal flag behind that ejection port that is raised by the rim of a chambered cartridge—and a magazine disconnector that prevents firing if a magazine is not fully seated and locked in the magazine well. The stamped metal magazine holds eight rounds and utilizes a plastic follower.

The Bersa’s polymer frame has a fairly unique and modern appearance. Made of what Bersa calls High Impact polymer, it felt light but rigid. Applying pressure to the sides of the empty magazine well yielded no discernible flexing. Molded into the dustcover is a 1 1/2-inch section of Picatinny rail. Behind that, and just above the front of the trigger guard, an arrowhead-shaped portion of the frame has molded-in stippling in a fine, mosaic-like pattern. The stippled area tapers back toward the shooter and serves to guide the trigger finger into a good “ready” position outside and above the trigger well. It is present on both the right and left side of the frame. Also featuring stippling are two polygonal sections on each of the grip panels, providing purchase for the tips of the three supporting fingers. Front- and backstrap molding consists of shallow grooves that curve around the grip and angle down from back to front. The frame seems well made and the molding is precise and consistent.

Action Type: striker-fired, semi-automatic center-fire pistol

title: Want To Buy:  Looking for firearm parts and gunsmithing tools.
postcontent:
I am going to keep this short. If you require more info, please email me.
My name is Dave,
I am the owner of DR's Coins & Collectibles in Lakeland FL. I don't have a store front right now, I mainly deal at Coin Shows and on the internet.  Currently I am enrolled in an online college program at Penn Foster to earn a Gunsmithing Degree and get my FFL. I have been working on this degree since August 2012 and I should be done in July of 2013. 
I am trying to aquire, either cheap or for free, unwanted gun parts, and certain tools that are useful in the gunsmithing field. I currently build custom AR-15's and then sell them in a private sale(I can send you photo's of one of my most recent builds). Some of the tools I am looking for are for stock making and grip making. 
Tools like Scroll Saws, sanders, wood chisels and hand lathes, stuff like that.
I'm not trying to be a cheap SOB and get free stuff, several unexpected situations came up in November that cost me over $5,000. On Thanksgiving, I got in a car accident and the other guy took off, I had to pay a $1,000 deductible for my car to get repaired, and I had to pay $4,750 in medical expenses, and a rental car. Now with Christmas right around the corner, I am just trying to reduce my expenses for a month or two, and be able to further my education and small business plan.

If you can be of any help, I would really appreciate it. If I don't move out of FL, I hope to open my business in Lakeland or Auburndale in late 2013.
You can check my DBA on SunBiz. Org, but it is DR's Coins & Currency. All the info is still accurate.
Please call or email me with your name and what you have. I can drive to meet you. I live in Lakeland. 
The only stuff I really have for trade is Bass fishing tackle.
Thanks very much for reading this. Have a great and safe holiday season.

title: For Sale/Trade:  2x QSC K12, LED effects lighting, Galaxian 3D
postcontent:
Two QSC K12 12" powered speakers. 

Perfect for small events. Enable DEEP mode, get more bass without muddying the sound, no need for a sub. Perfect for mobile gigs. Far more convenient than hauling passive cabs, extra cables, and amps around. Not heavy - I haul them in one trip.

Doubles as a monitor. Sometimes I do events where we end up with no monitor, poor monitors, or monitors where I can't control the levels (I like monitors low enough that I can hear the mains as well, and I don't need the monitors blasting my ears all night). Bringing along a K12 takes up little room, but has more than enough power, and gives pristine sound. Angled side allows it to be a wedge as well as sit on a chair or stand. Played with Heavygrinder at a gig where the promoter forgot to have mons set up at all; she appreciated borrowing a K12 for her set.

The size belies their power. High SPL from a little 12", with excellent clarity. Does not distort at high volumes, unlike the EONs I've had that sounded like laptop speakers past 1/2 volume and barely cut it for house parties. I've shown up to gigs where the 15" mains didn't have the power and clarity of the K12s, so we just swapped them out.

Input matrix allows two simultaneous inputs; it's basically a two channel mixer. Also has ports for daisy chaining.

EXT SUB mode for use with external subs without needing a crossover. VOCAL BOOST mode for public speaking gigs.

Triples as part of an awesome home theater system. Had them hooked up to the PS3 and DVD player, with video going to the projector. Puts the "theater" in "home theater".

Purchased new a little over a year ago. Pristine condition. Not even dusty. Only flaws are some scrapes in the paint on the sides from normal use.

Asking $1500 or best offer. 
Willing to ship within the US. 
Open to trades for quality modern firearms (e.g., M1A, MPA MAC clones, "tactical" 22s), nice somewhat-portable synths (e.g., Nord G1), Ecler Nuo 4 (not 4.0), and/or a portable audio/MIDI to USB/FireWire interface with low latency (e.g., Komplete Audio 6).

I also have several lights for sale or trade.

2x ADJ Mystic LED
1x ADJ Quad LED
1x Chauvet Galaxian 3D R/G laser
1x On Stage Stands lighting tree

Everything is near mint. Comes with original boxes, manuals still in the wrap, cables, etc. Bought it all in an emergency (lighting guy bailed last minute for a mobile gig, so I went out to GC and bought the minimal amount of lights we needed). They've since sat in their boxes, all of which are inside a crate, which itself is inside air conditioned storage. I have since gotten together with a top-notch group of lighting wizards, and most of the clubs I play already have their own lighting.

Everything is DMX-aware. I chose these units for their wide coverage. The Mystics will strobe as well as moonflower, which is pretty cool.  

$800 or best offer takes all the lights and tree. Paid $1100.
Willing to ship within the US. 
Open to trades for quality modern firearms (e.g., M1A, MPA MAC clones, "tactical" 22s), nice somewhat-portable synths (e.g., Nord G1), Ecler Nuo 4 (not 4.0), and/or a portable audio/MIDI to USB/FireWire interface with low latency (e.g., Komplete Audio 6).

Will post pics over the weekend.

The PMR-30 is a light weight, full size pistol chambered for the flat-shooting .22Magnum cartridge (.22WMR). The PMR-30 operates on a unique hybrid blowback/locked-breech system. It uses a double stack magazine of a new design that holds 30 rounds and fits completely in the grip of the pistol. The trigger is a crisp single action with an over-travel stop. PMR30 disassembles for cleaning by removal of a single pin
